content:
Prioritize, distribute, and assign records to teams who share workloads. Access queues from list views. Queue members can jump in to take ownership of any record in a queue. They’re available for cases, contact requests, leads, orders, custom objects, service contracts, and knowledge article versions.

You can manually add a record to a queue by changing the record’s owner to the queue. Or, an assignment rule can add cases or leads to a queue based on specific record criteria. Records remain in a queue until they’re assigned an owner. Any queue members or users higher in a role hierarchy can take ownership of records in a queue.

Create queues to prioritize and assign records to teams that share workloads. Create routing configurations to determine how work items are routed to agents. Use them to prioritize the relative importance and size of work items from your queues.

Queues help manage leads, cases, contact requests, and custom objects. Omni-Channel supercharges your queues to route work items to agents in real time. Agents don’t have to select work items manually from queues because Omni-Channel routes work items to agents automatically and in real time!

Create a custom report type before building reports on queue members.
title: Managing Queues in Service Cloud
